arch:note.arch:string: The purpose of the daily journal was to record the activities taking place in a trench each day. This included which loci were excavated, how and why loci were excavated and the ongoing impressions of the relationships among loci. It should be noted that journals record the actions, impressions and ideas of trench supervisors during the excavations. They are not, therefore, the final interpretations or syntheses of the emerging data.

arch:internalDocument.arch:string:
August 10, 2001

We started to sweep because the trench is full of dirt after a week of not digging.

I decided to expand L4037 because it seems to be connected to me.

There is also another slag looking thing under L4036 with an opening elevation of 93.28 L5054.

I took off L4037 there was a fish net weight (broken) there.

Also we are continuing L4042 from the part that we stopped.

I opened a locus for the river conglomerate or slag pit looking feature at the very SW corner (L4054). It looks very similar to L4048 opening elevation 93.28.

I dug deeper within the rocks in L4006 in order to close the locus. At the bottom we found some pottery. I am going to take a picture and mark it as L4006 because I couldn't find out what it is. It doesn't seem like anything after we took off the rock circle.

We also took the alignment L4046 out and also I opened a new locus for the pile of rocks at the East of L4046. Because it doesn't seem the collapse anymore L4055.

Then I expanded L4033 to West a little and took that off too. (It seems same)

Now we are taking L4055 off after taking the photos. Also I took some photos of L4042 because it seems there are some mud brick there, also the edge of the wall.

After the breakfast we took off L4023 possible wall and collapse or a feature.

Now we are sweeping the trench. It is interesting that the part under L4026 is different than the rest. I guess L4026 was sealing that part.

There was some reddish material in the SouthEast 1/4. Now we still have it under a rock. So I will take a photo, spot it to the day pan, Munsell and took it off.

Also this rock seems to be painted to white. I marked it in L4052. The color of the pink stuff under is 7.5 YR 7/4 Pink. I don't know maybe I should open a locus for this but I think I gave all of the info necessary. (The elev is: 93.67 on top of the rock). (It is clay looking, compact, as a block of clay put there) I will take another photo with the surrounding. (It is under L4052) Also there are small rocks (one or two) next to the bottom of the feature.

I also open L4056 for the rocks came under L4052 at the North side of the locus. It seems to be one of these regular rock piles with 10-20 rocks, sized 5cm to 20cm. Various rows and possibly only on course. Opening elev of L4056: West 93.59, East 93.57

Also we cut the higher part next to the oven and we found some carbon pieces there. In the pottery bag of L4045 today: We collected the pottery visible between L4046 and L4035 into this bag.

The bottom of L4048 seems curved, circular. So I am quite sure that this is a pit but still don't know. All things came as a whole and took sample from the broken stuff. There are 3 rocks on the East side.

I opened L4057 because I removed some features so I changed the fill underneath L4045 and L4052. It is an arbitrary change that I don't see any difference in soil.

Also opened L4058 for the harder part next to the South Baulk possibly abutting L4030. Also there is a possibility that I am seeing some lines parallel to wall L4030 on this locus.
